|CKB                        How to purchase a new Ship
|WKB------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|YKOWe are currently offering four different types of ships:
           |WKOCog, Galley, Catamaran, and Carrack.


|YKOYour first step is to |YKB"purchase" |YKOone of the ship types at the ship shop
located: 5:s,e,s,3:e,n,e,s of COT.

         |GKBA cog costs 120,000 gold.
         A galley cost 180,000 gold.
         A carrack costs 400,000 gold.

|YKOThe catamaran is only available at the Wayfarian ship shop on Talamh Darag.

To buy a ship, simply |YKB'request application' |YKOin the ship shop. Then |YKB'read
application' |YKOto see the information required. Please |YKB"fillin [number] [text]"
|YKOto complete the application. When you are finished, |YKB"turnin" |YKOthe application
at a ship shop.

Congratulations, then you own a new ship, which will be placed in port for you.


                               |CKBOrders
|WKB------------------------------------------------------------------------------
         |YKOA small list of orders you can give while onboard ship.

|CKBCaptains Quarters
|WKB----------------------
|YKOThe captain can create his own room description by typing |YKB"rename <description>"
|YKOwhere the description is one continous line with a return at the end.
Also, anyone one in the room can custom emote by typing |YKB"em <stuff>".


|CKBBridge
|WKB----------------------
This is where the captain can do the most.

|YKBdemote         |YKO- Demotes a captain to a passenger
|YKBdock           |YKO- Orders the crew to dock the ship.
|YKBforbid         |YKO- Repeals a passenger's boarding privilges
|YKBfurl           |YKO- Orders the crew to pull down the sails.
|YKBhoist          |YKO- Orders the crew to raise the sails.
|YKBlist           |YKO- Gives you a current list of the ship's passengers
                  or captains.
|YKBpeer           |YKO- To look overboard and see what's around.
|YKBpermit         |YKO- Grants a player permission to board your ship only
|YKBpromote        |YKO- Promotes a passenger to captain (can sail the ship)
|YKBpush off       |YKO- Orders the crew to pull away from the dock.
|YKBsail <dir>     |YKO- To move the ship.
|YKByell           |YKO- Yells a message to the area outside your ship


|CKBDeck
|WKB----------------------
|YKBdisembark      |YKO- Disembark the ship
|YKBpeer           |YKO- To look overboard and see what's around.


While onboard, you can type |YKB"orders" |YKOin any room to see the list of orders
you may give while in that room. Not all rooms have orders to report.
